  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "When you make a purchase through KrazyBee, the process of paying installments typically involves the following steps:\n\n1. **Verification and Approval:** After you make a purchase, KrazyBee verifies your details and approves the loan for the amount required. This might involve uploading documents and going through a verification process.\n\n2. **Down Payment:** You may be required to make a small down payment at the time of purchase.\n\n3. **EMI Calculation:** KrazyBee will calculate your Equated Monthly Installments (EMIs) based on the loan amount, interest rate, and loan tenure.\n\n4. **EMI Payment:** You will receive a schedule of payments detailing when and how much you need to pay each month. The payment is generally done via online methods such as net banking, debit cards, or other online payment gateways.\n\n5. **Repayment:** Ensure you make the payments on time every month as per the schedule. KrazyBee will typically send reminders and alerts for due payments.\n\n6. **Tracking:** You can track your payment history and upcoming payments via KrazyBee\u2019s mobile app or website.\n\nIt is important to read all the terms and conditions carefully before finalizing the purchase, so you are aware of the interest rates, repayment terms, and any penalties for late payments. If you have any specific questions or need assistance, it is best to contact KrazyBee's customer support directly.",
